  598:<h2 id="connect"><a class="anchor" href="#connect"></a>Connect to the database</h2>
  599-<div class="sectionbody">
  600-<div class="paragraph">
  601:<p>Connect to a database by creating a <code>Driver</code> object and providing a URL and an authentication token.
  602:Once you have a <code>Driver</code> instance, use the <code>.verifyConnectivity()</code> method to ensure that a working connection can be established.</p>
  603-</div>
  604-<div class="listingblock nocollapse">
  --
  607-
  608-import org.neo4j.driver.AuthTokens;
  609:import org.neo4j.driver.GraphDatabase;
  610-
  611-public class App {
  --
  618-        final String dbPassword = "&lt;password&gt;";
  619-
  620:        try (var driver = GraphDatabase.driver(dbUri, AuthTokens.basic(dbUser, dbPassword))) {
  621:            driver.verifyConnectivity();
  622:            System.out.println("Connection established.");
  623-        }
  624-    }
  --
  635-<div class="sectionbody">
  636-<div class="paragraph">
  637:<p>Run a Cypher query with the method <code>Driver.executableQuery()</code>.
  638-Do not hardcode or concatenate parameters: use placeholders and specify the parameters as a map through the <code>.withParameters()</code> method.</p>
  639-</div>
  --
  707-<div class="sectionbody">
  708-<div class="paragraph">
  709:<p>Unless you created them with <code>try-with-resources</code> statements, call the <code>.close()</code> method on all <code>Driver</code> and <code>Session</code> instances to release any resources still held by them.</p>
  710-</div>
  711-<div class="listingblock">
  --
  772-<dt><a id="bookmark"></a>bookmark</dt>
  773-<dd>
  774:<p>A <em>bookmark</em> is a token representing some state of the database. By passing one or multiple bookmarks along with a query, the server will make sure that the query does not get executed before the represented state(s) have been established.</p>
  775-</dd>
  776-<dt><a id="transaction_function"></a>transaction function</dt>
  777-<dd>
  778:<p>A transaction function is a callback executed by an <code>executeRead</code> or <code>executeWrite</code> call. The driver automatically re-executes the callback in case of server failure.</p>
  779-</dd>
  780:<dt><a id="Driver"></a>Driver</dt>
  781-<dd>
  782:<p>A <a href="https://neo4j.com/docs/api/java-driver/current/org.neo4j.driver/org/neo4j/driver/Driver.html"><code>Driver</code></a> object holds the details required to establish connections with a Neo4j database.</p>
  783-</dd>
  784-</dl>
